---
// ArchitectureLayers.astro — Pure CSS/HTML expandable architecture diagram
// Uses <details>/<summary> for zero-JS interactivity
---

<div class="arch-wrap">
  <h3 class="arch-title">The Architecture — 3 Layers</h3>
  <p class="arch-sub">Click each layer to see what's inside.</p>

  <div class="arch-stack">
    <!-- Layer 1: Brain -->
    <details class="layer layer--amber">
      <summary class="layer-header">
        <span class="layer-icon">🧠</span>
        <div class="layer-info">
          <span class="layer-name">The Brain</span>
          <span class="layer-tech">LangGraph Orchestrator</span>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-pills">
          <span class="pill pill--amber">Plan Step</span>
          <span class="pill pill--amber">Act Step</span>
          <span class="pill pill--amber">Observe</span>
          <span class="pill pill--amber">Refine</span>
        </div>
        <span class="layer-arrow">▼</span>
      </summary>
      <div class="layer-body">
        <p>LangGraph models the reasoning loop as a <strong>state machine</strong>. Each node is a step. Edges define transitions. The graph decides when to loop, when to escalate, and when to stop.</p>
        <pre class="layer-code"><code>graph = StateGraph(AgentState)
graph.add_node("plan", plan_step)
graph.add_node("act", execute_tool)
graph.add_node("observe", interpret_results)
graph.add_node("refine", adjust_strategy)

graph.add_conditional_edges("observe",
  should_refine,
  {"{"}True: "refine", False: "__end__"{"}"}
)
graph.add_edge("refine", "plan")  # ← The loop</code></pre>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="connector">
      <svg width="24" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 20"><path d="M12 0 L12 20 M6 14 L12 20 L18 14" stroke="#475569" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
    </div>

    <!-- Layer 2: Hands -->
    <details class="layer layer--cyan">
      <summary class="layer-header">
        <span class="layer-icon">⚡</span>
        <div class="layer-info">
          <span class="layer-name">The Hands</span>
          <span class="layer-tech">Python Toolset</span>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-pills">
          <span class="pill pill--cyan">Data Validator</span>
          <span class="pill pill--cyan">Rule Searcher</span>
          <span class="pill pill--cyan">Limit Checker</span>
        </div>
        <span class="layer-arrow">▼</span>
      </summary>
      <div class="layer-body">
        <p>Small Python tools the agent calls during the ACT phase. Each one does one job and returns structured data — no free-text guessing.</p>
        <pre class="layer-code"><code>@tool
def check_value(item_id, field, limit):
    """Check if a field exceeds its limit."""
    value = database.get(item_id, field)
    return {"{"}"value": value,
            "limit": limit,
            "exceeded": value > limit{"}"}  </code></pre>
      </div>
    </details>

    <!-- Connector -->
    <div class="connector">
      <svg width="24" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 20"><path d="M12 0 L12 20 M6 14 L12 20 L18 14" stroke="#475569" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
    </div>

    <!-- Layer 3: Guardrails -->
    <details class="layer layer--green">
      <summary class="layer-header">
        <span class="layer-icon">🛡</span>
        <div class="layer-info">
          <span class="layer-name">The Guardrails</span>
          <span class="layer-tech">Azure AI Search + RAG</span>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-pills">
          <span class="pill pill--green">Vector DB</span>
          <span class="pill pill--green">Cite-or-Reject</span>
          <span class="pill pill--green">Decision Logger</span>
        </div>
        <span class="layer-arrow">▼</span>
      </summary>
      <div class="layer-body">
        <p>Your rules live in a searchable database. The agent finds the right rule by meaning, not keywords. The <strong>cite-or-reject</strong> guardrail: no rule cited, no flag allowed. Every decision is logged.</p>
        <pre class="layer-code"><code># Guardrail: reject any flag without a cited rule
if not result.cited_rule:
    return "REJECTED: cite which rule was broken"

# If cited → log and flag
decision_log.record(
    record_id=item.id,
    issue=result.description,
    rule=result.cited_rule,
    confidence=result.confidence
)</code></pre>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .arch-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border: 1px solid #334155;
  }
  .arch-title {
    color: #f1f5f9; font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }
  .arch-sub {
    color: #64748b; font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem; font-family: monospace;
  }

  .arch-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .connector {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 4px 0;
  }

  /* Layer (details/summary) */
  .layer {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid #334155;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    transition: border-color 0.3s, background 0.3s;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .layer[open] { border-color: #475569; }
  .layer--amber[open] { border-color: #f59e0b40; background: rgba(245,158,11,0.03); }
  .layer--cyan[open]  { border-color: #06b6d440; background: rgba(6,182,212,0.03); }
  .layer--green[open] { border-color: #4ade8040; background: rgba(74,222,128,0.03); }

  .layer-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .layer-header::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .layer-header::marker { content: ''; }

  .layer-icon { font-size: 1.3rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .layer-info { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-width: 120px; }
  .layer-name { color: #e2e8f0; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .layer-tech { color: #64748b; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.6rem; }

  .layer-pills {
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 4px;
    margin-left: auto;
  }
  .pill {
    font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.55rem;
    padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 5px;
  }
  .pill--amber { background: rgba(245,158,11,0.1); color: #f59e0b; border: 1px solid rgba(245,158,11,0.2); }
  .pill--cyan  { background: rgba(6,182,212,0.1); color: #06b6d4; border: 1px solid rgba(6,182,212,0.2); }
  .pill--green { background: rgba(74,222,128,0.1); color: #4ade80; border: 1px solid rgba(74,222,128,0.2); }

  .layer-arrow {
    color: #475569;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    transition: transform 0.3s;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .layer[open] .layer-arrow { transform: rotate(180deg); }

  .layer-body {
    padding: 0 16px 16px;
  }
  .layer-body p {
    color: #94a3b8;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .layer-body strong { color: #e2e8f0; }

  .layer-code {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 12px 14px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    overflow-x: auto;
    border: 1px solid #334155;
  }
  .layer--amber .layer-code { background: rgba(245,158,11,0.04); color: #fbbf24; }
  .layer--cyan .layer-code  { background: rgba(6,182,212,0.04); color: #22d3ee; }
  .layer--green .layer-code { background: rgba(74,222,128,0.04); color: #86efac; }

  .layer-code code {
    background: transparent !important;
    padding: 0 !important;
    color: inherit !important;
    font-size: inherit !important;
  }
</style>
